        <div class="annotation"><div xmlns="">Don Cristóbal de León, disciple and ally of &quot;the author Ayala,&quot; imprisoned by the royal administrator for defending the natives of the province. &quot;I will hang you, vile Indian!&quot; threatens the administrator. &quot;For my people I will suffer in these stocks,&quot; Don Cristóbal replies.</div></div>
